text: Alan Wilks (born 5 October 1946) was a footballer with Queens Park Rangers. He signed in 1965 from ChelseaNigel's Webspace - FKS 1968/69 Wonderful World of Soccer Stars - Q.P.R and made his debut in the 2–2 draw with Brighton in December 1966. He was a striker and scored all 5 goals in a League Cup game against Oxford United in 1967.QPR REPORT: Ex-QPR Birthdays: Alan WIlks Turned 60...Steve Slade Turns 31 Alan played 50 league games for QPR scoring 14 goals before moving to Gillingham in 1971.
